<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>k = 100</code></pre>
<pre class="code-output documenter-example-output" id="var-k">100</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>m = 1</code></pre>
<pre class="code-output documenter-example-output" id="var-m">1</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>ω = sqrt(k/m)</code></pre>
<pre class="code-output documenter-example-output" id="var-ω">10.0</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'># Simple Harmonic Oscillator Problem
import OrdinaryDiffEq as ODE, Plots

#Initial Conditions</code></pre>


<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>x0 = 0</code></pre>
<pre class="code-output documenter-example-output" id="var-x0">0</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>v0 = 2</code></pre>
<pre class="code-output documenter-example-output" id="var-v0">2</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>tspan = (0, 4*pi/ω)</code></pre>
<pre class="code-output documenter-example-output" id="var-tspan">(0, 1.2566370614359172)</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>A = x0</code></pre>
<pre class="code-output documenter-example-output" id="var-A">0</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>B = v0/ω

#Define the problem</code></pre>
<pre class="code-output documenter-example-output" id="var-B">0.2</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>function harmonicoscillator(ddu, du, u, ω, t)
    ddu .= -ω^2 * u
end

#Pass to solvers</code></pre>
<pre class="code-output documenter-example-output" id="var-harmonicoscillator">harmonicoscillator (generic function with 1 method)</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>prob = ODE.SecondOrderODEProblem(harmonicoscillator, 
                                 [v0], 
                                 [x0], 
                                 tspan, 
                                 ω)</code></pre>
<pre class="code-output documenter-example-output" id="var-prob">�[38;2;86;182;194mODEProblem�[0m with uType �[38;2;86;182;194mRecursiveArrayTools.ArrayPartition{Int64, Tuple{Vector{Int64}, Vector{Int64}}}�[0m and tType �[38;2;86;182;194mFloat64�[0m. In-place: �[38;2;86;182;194mtrue�[0m
timespan: (0.0, 1.2566370614359172)
u0: ([2], [0])</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>sol = ODE.solve(prob, ODE.DPRKN6())</code></pre>
